// // This module implements a 1-bit DRAM cell with a data input (D), a control input (WE - write enable), and an output (Q). When WE is high, the value of D should be written into the cell. However, when WE is low, Q should reflect the currently stored value in the cell.
module dram_cell (
    input wire D,
    input wire WE,
    output reg Q
);
    always @(WE or D) begin
        if (WE) begin
            Q <= D; // Write data to the cell
        end
        // When WE is low, retain the current value of Q
    end
endmodule
